The assignments of 1 H and 13 C NMR spectra of 1 (methanol- d 4 ) are shown in Table 1 . Two sets of o -coupling pattern protons in the aromatic field ( δH 7.42, 2H, br d, J = 8.5 Hz, H-2 ′ and H-6 ′ ; 6.95, 2H, br d, J = 8.5 Hz, H-3 ′ and H-5 ′ ; 6.22, 1H, d, J = 2.0 Hz, H-6; 6.18, 1H, d, J = 2.0 Hz, H-8) and an ABX coupling system protons ( δH 5.43, 1H, dd, J = 13.0, 3.0 Hz, H-2; 3.16, 1H, dd, J = 17.0, 13.0 Hz, H-3ax; 2.76, 1H, dd, J = 17.0, 3.0 Hz, H-3eq) suggested the presence of a flavanone skeleton. The pseudo-axial or equatorial orientation of H 2 -3 were determined by the large coupling constant ( J = 13.0 Hz) between H-2 and H-3ax ( Funari et al., 2011 ). The methoxy proton δH 3.81 (3H, s) and carbon δC 55.8 resonances were observed, and the methyl proton was long-range coupled with the C-4 ′ ( δC 161.6), which showed that the aglycone moiety was isosakuranetin. In 13 C NMR spectra, six glucosidic carbons ( δC 101.2, 74.7, 77.9, 71.6, 75.6, 65.4, C-Glc-1–6) and two carbonyl carbons ( δC 170.3 and 168.8) were observed as a feature of this compound ( Agrawal 1992 ;
Selenge et al., 2014
). The glucose proton [ δH 4.48 (1H, dd, J = 11.5, 2.5 Hz, H-Glc-6), 4.25 (1H, dd, J = 11.5, 7.5 Hz, H-Glc-6)] and carbon ( δC 65.4, C-Glc-6) resonances were lower field shifted than those of isosakuranetin 7- O -glucopyranoside ( 3 ), showing the presence of an acyl moiety at C-Glc-6 of 1 . The molecular formula of 1 was determined to be C 25 H 26 O 13 based on HRFABMS data (positive): m / z 535.1455 [M+H] + (calcd for C 25 H 27 O 13 : 535.1451). The molecular formula for an additional C 3 H 2 O 3 corresponded to a malonyl moiety compared with isosakuranetin 7- O -glucopyranoside ( 3 ) (C 22 H 24 O 10 ). In a heteronuclear multiple bond correlation (HMBC) spectrum ( Fig. 2 ), H-Glc-6 was long-range coupled with the malonyl carbon at δC 168.8. These 1 H and 13 C NMR chemical shifts of Glc-6 and HMBC correlation showed a malonyl group bond to C-Glc-6. In an electronic CD (ECD) spectrum ( Fig. 3 ), the negative Cotton effect at 286 nm showed the (2 S )-absolute configuration of 1 ( Gaffield, 1970 ; Slade et al., 2005 ). HPLC sugar analysis after acid hydrolysis indicated that the sugar moiety was D-glucopyranose. The coupling constant of the anomeric proton ( J = 7.5 Hz) suggested its β- configuration. Therefore, 1 was determined to be (2 S )-isosakuranetin 7- O -β- D-(6 ′′ - O -malonyl)glucopyranoside, as shown in Fig. 1 .

